HEADWORD: Omahas
<hw>O"ma*has"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Omaha</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A
tribe of Indians who inhabited the south side of the Missouri River.
They are now partly civilized and occupy a reservation in
Nebraska.</def>⟦br⟧
